## Next Steps

> [!NOTE]
> The spatial analysis is **Phase 6** of the 7-phase implementation plan. The remaining phases include:
> - **Phase 3**: Constructing composite Water Access Index (WAI) and Livelihood Asset Index (LAI)
> - **Phase 4**: Inferential statistical testing (Chi-Square, Kruskal-Wallis, Spearman correlations)
> - **Phase 5**: Regression modeling (Ordinal Logistic, Binary Logistic, OLS)
> - **Phase 7**: Final publication-quality figures and summary tables
>
> These phases will quantify the relationships that the spatial analysis has *visualized*, providing the statistical rigor needed for academic publication.
